None, session_id=None, code=None, command=None, session_reuse=False, **kwargs)`\n231:   - Verify: All parameters match tool schema\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T6.5** Implement execute method body\n234:   - Use `CodeInterpreterClient` with `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n235:   - Handle optional `language` parameter (default `python`)\n236:   - Handle optional `code` and/or `command` execution\n237:   - Handle optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, `code_interpreter_id`\n238:   - Return: JSON-serializable result object\n239:   - Verify: All parameters handled and result returned\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Phase 7: Documentation Files\n244: \n245: - [ ] **T7.1** Create README.md\n246:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md`\n247:   - Include: Plugin overview, installation instructions, usage examples\n248:   - Verify: File exists with content\n249: \n250: - [ ] **T7.2** Create GUIDE.md\n251:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md`\n252:   - Include: Detailed integration guide for Dify platform\n253:   - Verify: File exists with content\n254: \n255: - [ ] **T7.3** Create PRIVACY.md\n256:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md`\n257:   - Include: Privacy policy and data handling information\n258:   - Verify: File exists with content\n259: \n260: - [ ] **T7.4** Add icon files\n261:   - Files: `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png`, `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png`\n262:   - Verify: Both icon files exist\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ## Phase 8: Verification and Testing\n267: \n268: - [ ] **T8.1** Verify manifest structure\n269:   - Command: Parse `manifest.yaml` with YAML parser\n270:   - Check: All required fields present (`version`, `type`, `author`, `name`, `label`, `description`, `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource`, `plugins.tools`, `meta`)\n271:   - Verify: Manifest validates successfully\n272: \n273: - [ ] **T8.2** Verify provider descriptor structure\n274:   - Check: `provider/agentcube.yaml` has `identity`, `tools`, `extra.python.source`\n275:   - Verify: Provider descriptor complete\n276: \n277: - [ ] **T8.3** Verify tool schema structure\n278:   - Check: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` has all 8 parameters defined\n279:   - Check: Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required\n280:   - Check: Optional parameters marked correctly\n281:   - Verify: Tool schema complete\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T8.4** Verify Python module imports\n284:   - Command: `python -c \"import provider.agentcube\"` (with dependencies installed)\n285:   - Command: `python -c \"import tools.agentcube_code_interpreter\"` (with dependencies installed)\n286:   - Verify: Modules import without errors\n287: \n288: - [ ] **T8.5** Verify requirements.txt dependencies\n289:   - Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt` (dry-run or in venv)\n290:   - Verify: Dependencies install successfully\n291: \n292: - [ ] **T8.6** Verify file structure matches design.md\n293:   - Check: All 9 files from design.md file map present:\n294:     - `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`\n295:   - Verify: Complete file structure\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Acceptance Criteria\n300: \n301: 1. ✅ `main.py` runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n302: 2. ✅ `manifest.yaml` contains all required top-level keys and structure\n303: 3. ✅ Multilingual labels and descriptions present for 4 locales (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR)\n304: 4. ✅ Resource permissions include tool, model, endpoint, app, storage flags\n305: 5. ✅ Tool provider registered in `plugins.tools` list\n306: 6. ✅ Meta section specifies Python 3.12 runner with main entrypoint\n307: 7. ✅ `provider/agentcube.yaml` defines identity, tools list, and Python source\n308: 8. ✅ Tool schema declares all 8 parameters with correct types and forms\n309: 9. ✅ Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required=true\n310: 10. ✅ Language parameter offers select options: python, javascript, typescript\n311: 11. ✅ Provider class implements `_validate_credentials` with error handling\n312: 12. ✅ Tool class implements `_invoke` yielding JSON message\n313: 13. ✅ Tool class implements `execute` with all parameters matching schema\n314: 14. ✅ Requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n315: 15. ✅ Documentation files present: README.md, GUIDE.md, PRIVACY.md\n316: 16. ✅ Icon files present: icon.png, icon-dark.png\n317: 17. ✅ .difyignore present with common ignore patterns\n318: 18. ✅ File structure matches design.md (11 files total)\n319: 19. ✅ All YAML files parse without syntax errors\n320: 20. ✅ Python modules import successfully with dependencies installed\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: **Notes:**\n325: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Dify plugin structure created)\n326: - Uses dify-plugin framework v0.4.x with agentcube-sdk v0.0.10+\n327: - Python runtime: 3.12 (specified in manifest.meta.runner)\n328: - Supports amd64 and arm64 architectures\n329: - Tool provider delegates to AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient\n330: - Plugin integrates with Dify's tool invocation framework\n331: - Credential validation raises ToolProviderCredentialValidationError on failure\n332: - Tool execution returns JSON-serializable results via create_json_message\n333: - File structure follows Dify plugin conventions from reference implementation\n334: \n335: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 335 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Plugin Bootstrap and Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create main.py entry point\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n  - Import: `Plugin`, `DifyPluginEnv` from `dify_plugin`\n  - Code: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n  - Verify: File exists with correct entry point\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with pinned dependencies\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n  - Add: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775886512386,"end":1775886512410}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886512413,"sessionID":"ses_284ea81b3ffenp7fNy7ULyxuaz","part":{"id":"prt_d7b15a9e1001T64DgQhFCtHADs","messageID":"msg_d7b1598b2001NWCmFWnwqklNSW","sessionID":"ses_284ea81b3ffenp7fNy7ULyxuaz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f23121f7a7a24ee7b75e7ea6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Dify Plugin\n2: \n3: AgentCube Code Interpreter integration for the Dify AI platform. Execute Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript code in secure Kubernetes sandboxes directly from your Dify applications.\n4: \n5: ## Features\n6: \n7: - **Secure Code Execution**: Run code in isolated Kubernetes sandbox environments\n8: - **Multiple Languages**: Support for Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript\n9: - **Session Management**: Reuse sessions for stateful interactions\n10: - **File Operations**: Upload and download files to/from the sandbox\n11: - **Command Execution**: Execute shell commands in addition to code\n12: \n13: ## Installation\n14: \n15: 1. Install the plugin dependencies:\n16:    ```bash\n17:    pip install -r requirements.txt\n18:    ```\n19: \n20: 2. Configure the plugin in your Dify instance by uploading the plugin package.\n21: \n22: ## Usage\n23: \n24: ### Basic Code Execution\n25: \n26: ```python\n27: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n28: \n29: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n30:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n31:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n32: ) as client:\n33:     result = client.execute(\"print('Hello, World!')\")\n34:     print(result[\"output\"])\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Session Reuse\n38: \n39: ```python\n40: client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n41:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n42:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n43:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n44: )\n45: try:\n46:     result = client.execute(\"x = 1 + 1\")\n47:     result2 = client.execute(\"print(x)\")  # x is still defined\n48: finally:\n49:     client.close()\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ### File Operations\n53: \n54: ```python\n55: with CodeInterpreterClient(\n56:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n57:     workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n58: ) as client:\n59:     # Upload a file\n60:     client.upload_file(\"data.txt\", b\"sample data\")\n61:     \n62:     # Download a file\n63:     content = client.download_file(\"data.txt\")\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ## Configuration\n67: \n68: The plugin requires the following configuration in Dify:\n69: \n70: - **Router URL**: Base URL of the AgentCube router service\n71: - **Workload Manager URL**: Base URL of the AgentCube workload manager service\n72: \n73: ## Requirements\n74: \n75: - Python 3.12 or later\n76: - Dify platform with plugin support\n77: - Access to AgentCube services (router and workload manager)\n78: - Kubernetes cluster with AgentCube deployed\n79: \n80: ## License\n81: \n82: Apache 2.0\n83: \n84: ## Support\n85: \n86: For issues and feature requests, please open an issue on the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube).\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Dify Plugin\n\nAgentCube Code Interpreter integration for the Dify AI platform. Execute Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript code in secure Kubernetes sandboxes directly from your Dify applications.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Secure Code Execution**: Run code in isolated Kubernetes sandbox environments\n- **Multiple Languages**: Support for Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript\n- **Session Management**: Reuse sessions for stateful interactions\n- **File Operations**: Upload and download files to/from the sandbox\n- **Command Execution**: Execute shell commands in addition to code\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Install the plugin dependencies:\n   ```bash\n   pip install -r requirements.txt\n   ```\n\n2. Configure the plugin in your Dify instance by uploading the plugin package.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/README.md","time":{"start":1775886512389,"end":1775886512412}}}}
